title: Access Datasets from the AURIN API
text: Letâ€™s recreate AURIN API R example using aurin. First, must add AURIN API username password R environment variable .Renviron file. aurin provides aur_register() function help step. choose set add_to_renviron = TRUE wonâ€™t need run step current machine restart R session. aur_browse() opens data catalogue AURIN default browser. Identify â€˜AURIN Open API IDâ€™ field â€˜Additional Infoâ€™ table dataset want download. example, public toilet 2017 dataset â€˜AURIN Open API IDâ€™ field "aurin:datasource-UQ_ERG-UoM_AURIN_DB_public_toilets". Note , datasets AURIN may â€˜AURIN Open API IDâ€™, meaning downloaded via API. Alternatively, may use aur_meta search datasets without leaving R console. Use aur_get() download dataset. Letâ€™s visualise data using ggplot2 package.  See find available datasets.
code: library(aurin)  # add_to_renviron = TRUE, so you won't need to run this step again on current machine. aur_register(username = "your-username", password = "your-password", add_to_renviron = T) aur_browse() library(notaurin) #> ! The `aurin` package is not affiliated with AURIN. Any issues or feedback related to the `aurin` package should be reported to https://github.com/asiripanich/aurin. If you would like to see the official AURIN API Guide please visit https://aurin.org.au/resources/aurin-apis/aurin-open-api-and-r/ meta <- aur_meta() #> â„¹ Creating AURIN WFS Client... #> Loading ISO 19139 XML schemas... #> Loading ISO 19115 codelists... #> Loading IANA mime types... #> No encoding supplied: defaulting to UTF-8. #> â„¹ Fetching available datasets... # print out the first five rows knitr::kable(head(meta)) # download this public toilet dataset. open_api_id <- "aurin:datasource-UQ_ERG-UoM_AURIN_DB_public_toilets" public_toilets <- aur_get(open_api_id = open_api_id) #> â„¹ Downloading 'aurin:datasource-UQ_ERG-UoM_AURIN_DB_public_toilets'... #> âœ” Finished! state_polygons <- aur_get(open_api_id = "aurin:datasource-AU_Govt_ABS-UoM_AURIN_DB_GeoLevel_ste_2016_aust") #> â„¹ Downloading 'aurin:datasource-AU_Govt_ABS-UoM_AURIN_DB_GeoLevel_ste_2016_aust'... #> âœ” Finished! state_polygons <- state_polygons[state_polygons$state_code_2016 %in% 1:8, ] # If you don't have the package you can install it with `install.packages("ggplot2")`. library(ggplot2) ggplot(public_toilets) +   geom_sf(data = state_polygons, fill = "antiquewhite") +   geom_sf(alpha = 0.05, aes(color = status)) +   labs(title = "Public toilets in Australia, 2017") +   scale_color_brewer(palette = "Dark2") +   theme_bw() +   guides(colour = guide_legend(override.aes = list(alpha = 1))) +   theme(panel.background = element_rect(fill = "aliceblue"))

title: Access Datasets from the AURIN API
text: many datasets need download, may want put CPUs work. code chucks show can download multiple datasets parallel using {furrr} {future} packages. First, setup workers - affects many datasets can download parallel time. maximum number workers machine can determined using future::availableCores(). Letâ€™s assume want first 10 rows datasets AURIN word â€œtoiletâ€ title. Extract AURIN open API ids download parallel.

title: Fetch AURIN dataset. â€” aur_get
text: open_api_id Character. can find layer names AURINâ€™s datasets browsing Data Catalogue. layer name found â€˜AURIN Open API IDâ€™ field datasetâ€™s metadata. crs default "EPSG:4326". Coordinate Reference System wish use params named list contains additional parameters used constructing WFS GetFeature request. useful know ID specific feature maximum number features want query. See examples . outputFormat default "application/json", see https://docs.geoserver.org/latest/en/user/services/wfs/outputformats.html available options.
